 meaning “offspring” in ذُرِّيَّة (ḏurriyya), can mean “to create”, needs no explanation. For the coloration meaning apparently ذَرَأ (ḏaraʔ) is the original and meant color specks figuratively strewn, ultimately becoming a dead metaphor like Russian сы́паться (sýpatʹsja) which is used for skin rashes and the like."},"ipa":null}